examples.korean: Looking at the crowds out shopping, you could be forgiven for thinking that everyone has plenty of money. 발음듣기 쇼핑하러 나온 사람들 무리를 보면 모든 사람이 돈이 많다고 생각해도 무리가 아닐 정도이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: Looking at the crowds out shopping, you could be forgiven for thinking that everyone has plenty of money. 발음

examples.korean: That may or may not be true. 발음듣기 그것은 사실일 수도 있고 사실이 아닐 수도 있다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: That may or may not be true. 발음

examples.korean: You can write ‘s/he’ as an epicene pronoun when you are not referring to men or women in particular. 발음듣기 특정한 남자나 여자를 가리키는 것이 아닐 때는 s/he를 양성 대명사로 쓸 수 있다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: You can write ‘s/he’ as an epicene pronoun when you are not referring to men or women in particular. 발음

examples.korean: You would be ill-advised to travel on your own. 발음듣기 당신 혼자서 여행하는 것은 좋은 생각이 아닐 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: You would be ill-advised to travel on your own. 발음

examples.korean: I’m sure he meant no offence when he said that. 발음듣기 분명히 그가 모욕을 주려고 그런 말을 한 것은 아닐 거야. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’m sure he meant no offence when he said that. 발음
